%U A397042 208,226,244,250,256,257,260,272,289,290,296,320,325,328,340,362,370,394,400,401,404,410,416,425
%N A397042 Numbers that can be written as the product of numbers of the form x^2 + 1.
%C A397042 Multiplicative semigroup generated by A002522.
%H A397042 Robert Israel, <a href="/A397042/b397042.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A397042 a(9) = 20 is a term because 20 = (1^2 + 1) * (1^2 + 1) * (2^2 + 1).
%p A397042 filter:= proc(n) option remember; local F;
%p A397042   if issqr(n-1) then return true fi;
%p A397042   ormap(t -> issqr(t-1) and filter(n/t), NumberTheory:-Divisors(n) minus {1,n});
%p A397042 end proc:
%p A397042 select(filter, [$1..1000]);
%Y A397042 Cf. A002522, A397044.
%K A397042 nonn
%O A397042 1,2
